Created attachment 559118
python.test.js.gz

User Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/13.0.782.220 Safari/535.1

Steps to reproduce:

Compiled CPython from C to JS using Emscripten (https://github.com/max99x/empythoned) and ran it from the command line in the mozilla-central JS engine with various flags. The build used in the tests is attached.


Actual results:

I got the following timings when running the script with various flags:

(none)       3.5s
-m           1.6s
-n           4.9s
-m -n        17.5s
-m -j -p     1.7s
-m -n -j -p  17.5s



Expected results:

When running the script with -n (type inference) flag, performance should not regress.
